<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Do factions actually work like they should?</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Tarquin">Tarquin</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 4:57 p.m. 16/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Do factions actually work like they should?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>A Necromancer is hated by all and can't even purchase from his own merchants, yet as I read on about faction standings, it is possible to change this. In Ak'anon, merchants won't sell to you (that is if you pick gnome like I did). So if I kill obsolete models in basements and kobolds outside, this should increase my faction standing and in end actually let me shop?

<P>I tried this and didn't work at all, was this function disabled in beta phase 4?
<P>Or am I doing something bad?
<P>Because way it is now people who start as gnome necromancers can't even purchase cloth armor.. I mean not the whole sets and its very hard to even buy a staff or other neat things.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
